$ Office Ribbon: File -> Options

table { ll
  → Microsoft/Office/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Options/General ☰ General options for working with → Microsoft/Office/Word[Word], → Microsoft/Office/Excel[Excel] etc.
  Display ☰ Word only(?): Change how → Microsoft/Office/Word/Object-Model/Document[document] content is displayed on the screen and when printed.
  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Options/Formulas[Formulas] ☰ Excel only(?): Change options realted to → Microsoft/Office/Excel/formulas calculation, performance, and error handling
  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Options/Data[Data] ☰ Excel only(?): Change options related to → development/Data import and → development/Data/analysis[data analysis]
  Proofing ☰ How text is corrected and formatted.
  Save ☰ How documents/→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Workbook[workbooks] are saved
  Language ☰ Set the Office Language Preferences
  Ease of Access ☰ Make Office application more accessible
  Advanced ☰ Advanced options
  → Microsoft/Office/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Options/Customize-Ribbon[Customize Ribbon] ☰ Customize the → Microsoft/Office/GUI/Ribbon[Ribbon]
  Quick Access Toolbar ☰ Customize the → Microsoft/Office/GUI/Quick-Access-Toolbar[Quick Access Toolbar] (see for example → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Quick-Access-Toolbar[here])
  → Microsoft/Office/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Options/Add-ins[Add-ins] ☰ View and manage → Microsoft/Office/add-in[Office Add-ins]
  → Microsoft/Office/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Options/Trust-Center ☰ Trying to keep computer secure and healthy.
table }
